node.text:
Would you try this? 😳💦 Devil’s Pool is a natural pool of water that’s situated atop of Victoria Falls, renown for being among the largest waterfalls in the world. Right on the edge of this massive waterfall, a calm pool of water forms.

After thousands of years of erosion, many rock pools have formed near the great Victoria Falls – and one of them… right on the very edge!

Would you dare to swim here? 💦

📽 @abenafrica #nature
📍Victoria Falls, Zimbabwe
🎶 Ikson - Apart

node.text:
Traditional Turkish coffee! Have you ever tried it? ☕️ Traditionally, a cup of Turkish coffee is brewed using a pan filled with sand, heated over an open flame. The sand-filled pan allows for total control over the heat. Cups left on the surface stay warm and the heat used for brewing can be adjusted by the depth of the coffee in the sand.

Turkish coffee is very finely ground coffee brewed by boiling. Any coffee bean may be used; arabica varieties are considered best, but robusta or a blend is also used. The coffee grounds are left in the coffee when served.

📽 @glamdapper #nature
📍Cappadocia, Turkey
🎶 STAY - The Kid LAROI & Justin Bieber

node.text:
Always living in the moment 💜 
Are you a dog or cat person? Swipe to see these @nature spots in the four seasons and save this post to visit with your pet! 📝

1. Grand Canyon National Park, Arizona
2. Zion National Park, Utah

4. Golden Gate Bridge, California
5. Sand Harbor Beach, Lake Tahoe, Nevada
6. Chino Hills State Park, California
7. San Francisco, California
8. Point Reyes National Seashore, California
9, 10. San Diego, California

Which seasonal picture is your favorite? 1-10?👇

📽 @sterlingsilvercat #nature

node.text:
Autumn walks in Finland 🍁✨ Have you visited this country in the fall season before?

Fall leaf colours, also known as "Ruska" to locals, characterises this season months in Finland. Landscapes are painted in vivid yellows, reds and browns, making every walk and hike even more magical.

Which picture is your favorite? Tag someone who loves @nature!

📷 @jukkarisikko #nature
📍Finland

node.text:
Hippos have the ability to lock their jaws at nearly 180 degree angles 😍 This feature, which makes a hippo look like it's yawning, is particularly important when hippos end up in conflict with other animals. The wide opening angle means that hippos can produce a bite force of 1,800 PSI—enough to break bones and snap wooden planks in two.

📽 @cincinnatizoo #nature
